- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a distributed control architecture for a string of agents to achieve trajectory tracking, velocity matching, and collision avoidance. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed control architecture can be applied to a group of autonomous agents, which can include robots. Hence, this paper can be categorized under robotics.
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper deals with a string of autonomous agents and proposes a distributed control architecture for them. This falls under the domain of multiagent systems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed control architecture involves decision-making and coordination among multiple agents, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the paper does not explicitly mention the use of machine learning, the proposed control architecture can potentially incorporate machine learning techniques for decision-making and coordination among agents. Hence, this paper can also be categorized under machine learning.
